---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="The Standards"
  description="What Morristown Eats is, and isn't. The rules behind this guide."
>
  <style>
    .v3-wrap {
      max-width: 620px;
      padding: 5rem 0 7rem;
    }
    .v3-not-this {
      background: var(--color-ink);
      color: var(--color-paper);
      padding: 2.5rem 2.5rem 2rem;
      margin-bottom: 3.5rem;
      box-shadow: 6px 6px 0 var(--color-rust);
    }
    .v3-not-this .not-label {
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      font-size: 0.7rem;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.15em;
      color: var(--color-mustard);
      display: block;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }
    .v3-not-this h1 {
      font-family: var(--font-display);
      font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
      color: var(--color-paper);
      line-height: 1.1;
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }
    .v3-not-this .not-list {
      list-style: none;
      padding: 0;
      margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
      columns: 2;
      column-gap: 1.5rem;
    }
    .v3-not-this .not-list li {
      font-family: var(--font-body);
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      line-height: 1.7;
      color: var(--color-paper);
      opacity: 0.75;
      padding-left: 1rem;
      position: relative;
    }
    .v3-not-this .not-list li::before {
      content: '✗';
      position: absolute;
      left: 0;
      color: var(--color-rust);
      font-size: 0.75rem;
    }
    .v3-not-this .what-it-is {
      font-family: var(--font-body);
      font-size: 1rem;
      line-height: 1.8;
      color: var(--color-paper);
      border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.2);
      padding-top: 1.25rem;
      margin-top: 0;
    }
    .v3-rules {
      list-style: none;
      padding: 0;
      margin: 0 0 4rem;
    }
    .v3-rule {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 2.5rem 1fr;
      gap: 1.25rem;
      padding: 2rem 0;
      border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-paper-dark);
      align-items: start;
    }
    .v3-rule:first-child {
      border-top: 2px solid var(--color-ink);
    }
    .v3-rule-num {
      font-family: var(--font-display);
      font-size: 2rem;
      color: var(--color-rust);
      line-height: 1;
      padding-top: 0.15rem;
    }
    .v3-rule-body h2 {
      font-family: var(--font-display);
      font-size: 1.3rem;
      color: var(--color-ink);
      margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
      line-height: 1.2;
    }
    .v3-rule-body p {
      font-family: var(--font-body);
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      line-height: 1.75;
      color: var(--color-ink-muted);
      margin: 0;
    }
    .v3-close {
      border-top: 3px solid var(--color-ink);
      padding-top: 2.5rem;
    }
    .v3-close p {
      font-family: var(--font-body);
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      line-height: 1.85;
      color: var(--color-ink);
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      font-style: italic;
    }
    .v3-close p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
    .v3-close strong {
      font-family: var(--font-display);
      font-size: 1.2rem;
      color: var(--color-rust);
      font-style: normal;
    }
    @media (max-width: 640px) {
      .v3-wrap { padding: 3rem 0 5rem; }
      .v3-not-this { padding: 2rem 1.5rem; }
      .v3-not-this .not-list { columns: 1; }
      .v3-rule { grid-template-columns: 2rem 1fr; gap: 1rem; }
    }
  </style>

  <div class="container">
    <div class="v3-wrap">

      <div class="v3-not-this">
        <span class="not-label">The Standards</span>
        <h1>First: what this isn't.</h1>
        <ul class="not-list">
          <li>A Yelp alternative</li>
          <li>A listing service</li>
          <li>A media business</li>
          <li>Sponsored content</li>
          <li>A star rating machine</li>
          <li>A PR organ</li>
          <li>Open submissions</li>
          <li>Trying to be comprehensive</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="what-it-is">
          What it is: an honest record of where to eat in Morristown.
          Backed by actual visits. Written down carefully. No financial
          relationships with anyone covered.
        </p>
      </div>

      <ol class="v3-rules">
        <li class="v3-rule">
          <span class="v3-rule-num">1</span>
          <div class="v3-rule-body">
            <h2>Visit before you write.</h2>
            <p>
              No profile goes up until we've eaten there and paid our own check.
              Restaurants confirmed open but not yet visited appear
              in the database marked clearly as unvisited — facts only, no editorial.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="v3-rule">
          <span class="v3-rule-num">2</span>
          <div class="v3-rule-body">
            <h2>No pay-to-play. Ever.</h2>
            <p>
              Not listing fees, placement fees, promoted profiles, or
              "partnership" content. This rule is the reason this guide exists
              separately from the local food coverage that already runs advertising.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="v3-rule">
          <span class="v3-rule-num">3</span>
          <div class="v3-rule-body">
            <h2>Independents first.</h2>
            <p>
              This guide exists to surface independently owned restaurants.
              National chains have plenty of coverage already. Local groups
              and independents don't. That asymmetry is the point.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="v3-rule">
          <span class="v3-rule-num">4</span>
          <div class="v3-rule-body">
            <h2>Say what you actually think.</h2>
            <p>
              If the food isn't worth recommending, the profile waits.
              Two mediocre visits and it doesn't go in at all.
              This is a recommendation list, not a directory.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="v3-rule">
          <span class="v3-rule-num">5</span>
          <div class="v3-rule-body">
            <h2>Be specific.</h2>
            <p>
              "Good vibes and great food" is not useful to anyone. What did you order?
              Was it actually good? What should someone else get?
              Write that down.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="v3-rule">
          <span class="v3-rule-num">6</span>
          <div class="v3-rule-body">
            <h2>No star ratings.</h2>
            <p>
              A 4.2 doesn't tell you whether to order the dumplings. A specific,
              honest recommendation does. This guide publishes those instead.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ol>

      <div class="v3-close">
        <p>
          Those are the rules. They don't change.
        </p>
        <p>
          We live here. We eat here constantly.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>

</BaseLayout>
